  07 Jan 2004; Brian Jackson <iggy@gentoo.org>
  redhat-sources-2.4.20.28.9.ebuild:
  remove all redhat-sources ebuilds, I'll remove the dir later

*redhat-sources-2.4.20.28.9 (07 Jan 2004)

  07 Jan 2004; <plasmaroo@gentoo.org> redhat-sources-2.4.18.24.8.0.ebuild,
  redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48-r1.ebuild, redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48.ebuild,
  redhat-sources-2.4.20.28.9.ebuild:
  Version bumped to address the security vulnerabilities in bugs #37292 and
  #37317. Old revisions were removed.

  03 Oct 2003; <plasmaroo@gentoo.org> redhat-sources-2.4.18.24.8.0.ebuild,
  redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48-r1.ebuild, redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48.ebuild:
  Fixed ebuilds to use the RPM eclass and not depend on rpm2targz. Thanks
  to Georgi Georgiev <chutz@chubaka.net> for the suggestion! Bug #30221.

*redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48-r1 (01 Mar 2003)

  01 Mar 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48-r1.ebuild:
  rpm2targz uses TMPDIR now. Thanks to: Jamie Anderson
  <gentoo.mail@jamieanderson.org> in bug #16586

*redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48 (23 Feb 2003)

  23 Feb 2003; Bruce A. Locke <blocke@shivan.org> redhat-sources-2.4.20.2.48.ebuild:
  Redhat 8.1 Beta 3 (Phoebe) kernel - 2.4.20.2.48.  This is an experimental
  kernel and care should be taken.  On a positive note this kernel compiles
  with Gentoo's rather stock gcc while 2.4.18.24.8.0 currently doesn't.

*redhat-sources-2.4.18.24.8.0 (17 Feb 2003)

  17 Feb 2003; Bruce A. Locke <blocke@shivan.org> redhat-sources-2.4.18.24.8.0.ebuild:
  Red Hat 8.0 kernel - 2.4.18-24.8.0 from updates

*redhat-sources-2.4.18-r4 (21 May 2002)

  17 Dec 2002; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org>:
  Make all kernel-sources SLOT="${KV}"

  06 Dec 2002; Rodney Rees <manson@gentoo.org> : changed sparc ~sparc keywords
 
  15 Jul 2002; Mark Guertin <gerk@gentoo.org>
  Added arch keywords (-ppc -sparc -sparc64)

  21 May 2002; Bruce A. Locke <blocke@shivan.org> redhat-sources-2.4.18-r4.ebuild :

  Redhat kernel 2.4.18-4 (official update to Redhat 7.3 kernel).  Older
  version removed due to potential instability and version conflict.
  
*redhat-sources-2.4.18.0.13 (28 Apr 2002)

  28 Apr 2002; Bruce A. Locke <blocke@shivan.org> redhat-sources-2.4.18.0.13.ebuild :

  Redhat kernel 2.4.18-0.13 (found in skipjack beta2)


